  "summary": "On-import console hijack exfiltrates logs to attacker Telegram bot",
  "details": "Package '0e' is unambiguously malicious. index.js replaces the global `console` with a Proxy on module evaluation that forwards every console call (info/warn/error/dir/etc.) to a hardcoded Telegram bot (token 1998266306:...) across multiple chat IDs, and additionally PUTs console.dir arguments to a hardcoded Firebase endpoint (iiilll.firebaseio.com) — see and static indicator a static pattern match (index.js:87,90). The module also embeds a third-party imgbb API key used to upload arbitrary data, index.js:14). Metadata is placeholder-grade: no README, author, or repository, matching the generic-placeholder-metadata-plus-network pattern. There is no plausible legitimate use for silently monkey-patching a host application's console to relay arguments to an attacker-controlled Telegram bot and Firebase — this is textbook data exfiltration plus credential redistribution.",
